---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - Skillsets.cc">
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <header class="mb-8 border-b border-border-ink pb-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-medium font-serif text-text-ink">About</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-lg font-serif text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        A skillset is a complete, battle-tested stack of Claude Code primitives that ship as one unit.
        The value is in the <em>orchestration</em> — how primitives are wired together, how context flows between them, and how the whole system behaves under real workloads.
      </p>

      <p>
        Every entry has shipped production software.
        <a href="/contribute" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">Submissions</a> require production proof, a structural audit, and an Opus qualitative review.
        Browse the registry or install via the <a href="/cli" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">CLI</a>.
      </p>

      <p>
        Built by <a href="https://github.com/supercollectible" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@supercollectible</a> using
        <a href="/skillset/@supercollectible/Valence" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">Valence</a> — the first skillset in the registry.
        Infrastructure is MIT-licensed. Individual skillsets are licensed by their authors.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
